Berkeley City Manager Paul Buddenhagen announced that the city will shut down hiring with limited exceptions through the summer of 2026. The 2026 general budget fund adopted by the council last year projected expenditures of $296 million, but current projections anticipate expenditures of $316 million. This overshoot is likely a result of increased salaries and overtime pay, a decrease in expected savings and the 134 vacant positions that were factored into the budget.
